    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-07-14T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-07-14T13:00:00-05:00" n="33"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.4131/1668: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-14T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 14, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 14—2:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>636. Had dinner with Oliver Stanley last night. He said he understood trade
                    agreement was fairly well settled with the exception of five or six points. I
                    said I have not been so advised.</p>
                <p>Everybody is planning to get out of town by the 29th of July. Is there anything I
                    can do on this?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
